\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Introduction:
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 This repository is developed for analyzing S-parameter data of GaN HEMTs. However, the provided programs are designed to be broadly applicable and are expected to function with transistors fabricated using other material technologies such as Si, GaAs, and Ga\u8322 O\u8323 .\

\f1\b How to Run:
\f0\b0 \
The repository includes three Python programs labeled 
\f1\b 1_
\f0\b0 , 
\f1\b 2_
\f0\b0 , and 
\f1\b 3_
\f0\b0 , which must be executed sequentially. Program 
\f1\b 1_
\f0\b0  is run first, its output serves as the input for Program 
\f1\b 2_
\f0\b0 , and the output from Program 
\f1\b 2_
\f0\b0  is subsequently used as the input for Program 
\f1\b 3_
\f0\b0 .\

\f1\b Program \'931_HEMT_ft_fmax_os_de-embedding\'94
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 This program performs Open\'96Short de-embedding using the scikit-rf (skrf) library to eliminate parasitic effects from the Device Under Test (DUT). It requires three measurement files (.s2p format):\
