\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Short structure\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The program generates several plots and produces a de-embedded DUT .s2p file after parasitic removal.\

\f1\b Program \'932_HEMT_de-embedding\'94
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 This program uses the de-embedded DUT .s2p files to extract various transistor parameters. The implemented methodology follows the approaches described in the publications listed below. The program outputs multiple plots along with a .csv file containing all extracted transistor parameters, which are later used as input for Program 3.\
Dambrine, Gilles, et al., 
\f2\i IEEE Transactions on Microwave Theory and Techniques
\f0\i0 , 36.7 (1988): 1151\'961159.\uc0\u8232 Berroth, Manfred, and Roland Bosch, 
\f2\i IEEE Transactions on Microwave Theory and Techniques
\f0\i0 , 39.2 (2002): 224\'96229.\uc0\u8232 Brady, Ronan G., Christopher H. Oxley, and Thomas J. Brazil, 
\f2\i IEEE Transactions on Microwave Theory and Techniques
\f0\i0 , 56.7 (2008): 1535\'961544.\

\f1\b Program \'933_HEMT_de-embedding_veri\'94
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 This program simulates the transistor\'92s equivalent circuit model and compares its frequency-dependent S-parameters with the Open\'96Short de-embedded measurement data. An iterative optimization procedure is implemented to achieve the best agreement between the measured data and the simulated circuit response.\
Sample .s2p files are also included in the repository to assist users in understanding the workflow.\
The 
\f1\b device.s2p
\f0\b0  file used in Program 1 corresponds to a transistor with a small gate periphery, whereas the datasets used in Programs 2 and 3 represent a transistor with a long gate periphery.\
